learn that is by failure.

44:29.217 --> 44:30.717
Ah, what a long day.

44:30.752 --> 44:33.586
I built this sled last night.

44:33.622 --> 44:36.656
Slept about two hours.

44:36.692 --> 44:38.458
Got up, went down the river.

44:38.493 --> 44:43.797
I was out on the jumble ice
and I spotted a bunch of
caribou and I was able to

44:43.832 --> 44:46.433
knock down this girl.

44:47.135 --> 44:49.336
I got a lot of
processing to do.

44:49.371 --> 44:55.308
I'm gonna turn this into,
uh, steaks, jerky, sausage,
ground meat, trapping bait.

44:57.579 --> 45:02.582
Pretty much every part of this
animal is usable whether it's
something practical for me to

45:02.617 --> 45:06.319
use for a tool, uh, my dogs
to get some extra nutrition.

45:07.989 --> 45:10.457
Everything on a caribou
is really usable.

45:10.492 --> 45:13.593
It's a great, great
resource out here.

45:14.863 --> 45:18.832
Well, this year,
I didn't get a moose so this
caribou is probably more

45:18.867 --> 45:21.935
important this year than it's
been in many, many years.

45:22.904 --> 45:26.906
It's a lot of work to do all
this, to build a sled, to go
out there to fight overflow.

45:26.942 --> 45:28.908
But this meat is the payoff.

45:29.411 --> 45:31.878
This is just the tip
of the iceberg for me.

45:31.913 --> 45:34.948
This is just my first of many,
many meals from this caribou.

45:37.219 --> 45:42.122
Living out in this country,
caribou, moose, salmon, none
of that gets delivered to you.

45:42.991 --> 45:45.859
The only reason you get
what you get out here
is you put the effort.

45:45.894 --> 45:47.394
The perseverance.

45:47.429 --> 45:49.462
Sometimes the suffering.

45:49.498 --> 45:54.567
I have to think, plan,
and work for the food
in a different way

45:55.170 --> 45:56.736
than most people do.

